### 4.3 TensorRT Runtime CUDA Graphs

**Automatic Capture** (runtime/generation.py):

TensorRT runtime can automatically capture and replay CUDA graphs:

```python
# Configuration
config = ExtendedRuntimePerfKnobConfig(
    cuda_graph_mode=True,           # Enable CUDA graphs
    cuda_graph_cache_size=10,       # LRU cache size
)

# Capture phase (automatic during first execution)
CUASSERT(cudart.cudaStreamBeginCapture(
    stream,
    cudart.cudaStreamCaptureMode.cudaStreamCaptureModeGlobal
))
context.execute_async_v3(stream)  # TensorRT engine execution
next_graph = CUASSERT(cudart.cudaStreamEndCapture(stream))[0]

# Instantiate graph
self.cuda_graph_instances[idx] = CUASSERT(
    cudart.cudaGraphInstantiate(next_graph, 0)
)[0]

# Upload to stream
CUASSERT(cudart.cudaGraphUpload(self.cuda_graph_instances[idx], stream))

# Replay phase (subsequent executions)
CUASSERT(cudart.cudaGraphLaunch(self.cuda_graph_instances[idx], stream))
```

**Ping-Pong Buffering**:
- Maintains two graph instances for smooth overlap
- While one graph executes, another can be captured/updated
- Prevents pipeline stalls

