## 5. Algorithmic Differences

### 5.1 Capture Strategy

| System | Strategy | Order | Pool Management |
|--------|----------|-------|-----------------|
| **vLLM** | On-demand capture during warmup | PIECEWISE first, then FULL | Global graph pool |
| **SGLang** | Batch capture at initialization | Reverse order (large→small) | Global pool + symmetric memory |
| **TensorRT-LLM** | Automatic on first execution | On-demand per batch config | Per-graph pool or shared |

### 5.2 Batch Matching

| System | Matching Algorithm | Padding | Fallback |
|--------|-------------------|---------|----------|
| **vLLM** | Exact match on BatchDescriptor | No padding | CUDAGraphMode.NONE |
| **SGLang** | Binary search + round up | Yes (to next captured size) | Eager execution |
| **TensorRT-LLM** | Exact match or round up | Optional (configurable) | Eager execution |

### 5.3 Mode Selection

| System | Modes | Dispatch Logic |
|--------|-------|----------------|
| **vLLM** | NONE, PIECEWISE, FULL, Dual-mode | Priority: FULL > PIECEWISE > NONE |
| **SGLang** | Standard, Piecewise | Priority: Piecewise > Standard > Eager |
| **TensorRT-LLM** | Decode-only | Decode check → Graph or Eager |

### 5.4 Memory Optimization

| Technique | vLLM | SGLang | TensorRT-LLM |
|-----------|------|--------|--------------|
| **Weak Reference Outputs** | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ |
| **Reverse Capture Order** | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |
| **Graph Pool Sharing** | ✅ | ✅ | ⚠️ (configurable) |
| **Memory Saver Adapter** | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |
| **Symmetric Memory (NCCL)** | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |

### 5.5 Variable Shape Handling

| System | Approach | Token Counts | Compilation |
|--------|----------|--------------|-------------|
| **vLLM** | PIECEWISE mode excludes attention | Fixed per capture | Optional (inductor) |
| **SGLang** | Piecewise graphs + torch.compile | ~20-50 sizes | Per-shape compile + graph |
| **TensorRT-LLM** | Decode-only restriction | N/A | TensorRT build-time |

### 5.6 Warmup Procedure

**vLLM**:
```python
# Warmup in NONE mode, then capture in target mode
for _ in range(num_warmups):
    _dummy_run(cudagraph_runtime_mode=NONE)
_dummy_run(cudagraph_runtime_mode=target_mode, is_graph_capturing=True)
```

**SGLang**:
```python
# Two warm runs, then capture
for _ in range(2):
    run_once()
with device.graph(graph):
    output = run_once()
```

**TensorRT-LLM**:
```python
# Automatic on first execution (no explicit warmup)
# Graph captured transparently if cuda_graph_mode=True
```

