## 8. Best Practices

### 8.1 When to Use Each System

**vLLM**:
- General-purpose LLM serving
- Mixed workloads (chat, completion, etc.)
- Need LoRA adapter support
- Want automatic mode selection

**SGLang**:
- Heavy prefix caching workloads
- Long prefill sequences (>1K tokens)
- Need maximum flexibility
- Can tolerate higher memory usage

**TensorRT-LLM**:
- Decode-heavy workloads
- Maximum single-request performance
- NVIDIA hardware optimization
- Production deployment

### 8.2 Configuration Recommendations

**vLLM**:
```python
